18/04/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government endorsed a new draft law Monday (17 April) on combating terrorism, and will forward it soon to parliament.
Justice Minister Cemil Cicek said that in preparing the bill, his ministry took into account input from the military, as well as international practices in the anti-terror effort.
According to media reports in Ankara, the draft law would penalise the parents of those involved in riots or armed rebel groups, among other measures.
(Focus - 18/04/06;
TurkishPress.com - 17/04/06)
